{
  "video_id": "i_wtaoHCw3k",
  "title": "What a scrapyard in Ghana can teach us about innovation | DK Osseo-Asare",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13650.0,
      "end_time": 16310.0,
      "text": "Come with me to Agbogbloshie,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16334.0,
      "end_time": 19120.0,
      "text": "a neighborhood in the heart of Accra,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19144.0,
      "end_time": 22648.0,
      "text": "named after a god that lives in the Odaw River."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23503.0,
      "end_time": 26317.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a slum, Old Fadama,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26341.0,
      "end_time": 30116.0,
      "text": "built on land reclaimed from the Korle Lagoon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 30140.0,
      "end_time": 32844.0,
      "text": "just before it opens into the Gulf of Guinea."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33908.0,
      "end_time": 38160.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a scrapyard here where people take apart all kinds of things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 38400.0,
      "end_time": 40370.0,
      "text": "from mobile phones to computers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 40394.0,
      "end_time": 43150.0,
      "text": "automobiles to even entire airplanes."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 43936.0,
      "end_time": 46475.0,
      "text": "Agbogbloshie&#39;s scrapyard is famous"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 46499.0,
      "end_time": 50978.0,
      "text": "because it has become a symbol of the downside of technology:"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 51200.0,
      "end_time": 53631.0,
      "text": "the problem of planned obsolescence."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 54203.0,
      "end_time": 59342.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s seen as a place where devices from around the world end their life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 59366.0,
      "end_time": 62167.0,
      "text": "where your data comes to die."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 63754.0,
      "end_time": 66524.0,
      "text": "These are the images that the media loves to show,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 66548.0,
      "end_time": 71370.0,
      "text": "of young men and boys burning wires and cables"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 71394.0,
      "end_time": 74115.0,
      "text": "to recover copper and aluminum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 74139.0,
      "end_time": 77538.0,
      "text": "using Styrofoam and old tires as fuel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 77562.0,
      "end_time": 80628.0,
      "text": "seriously hurting themselves and the environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 81993.0,
      "end_time": 84830.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a super-toxic process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 84108.0,
      "end_time": 87985.0,
      "text": "producing pollutants that enter the global ecosystem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 88900.0,
      "end_time": 90125.0,
      "text": "build up in fatty tissue"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 90149.0,
      "end_time": 92595.0,
      "text": "and threaten the top of the food chain."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 93950.0,
      "end_time": 96537.0,
      "text": "But this story is incomplete."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 98943.0,
      "end_time": 101801.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a lot we can learn from Agbogbloshie,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 101826.0,
      "end_time": 106354.0,
      "text": "where scrap collected from city- and nationwide is brought."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 106727.0,
      "end_time": 108449.0,
      "text": "For so many of us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 108473.0,
      "end_time": 110694.0,
      "text": "our devices are black boxes."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 110718.0,
      "end_time": 112133.0,
      "text": "We know what they do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 112157.0,
      "end_time": 114847.0,
      "text": "but not how they work or what&#39;s inside."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 115792.0,
      "end_time": 118277.0,
      "text": "In Agbogbloshie, people make it their business"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 118301.0,
      "end_time": 120358.0,
      "text": "to know exactly what&#39;s inside."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 120382.0,
      "end_time": 125918.0,
      "text": "Scrap dealers recover copper, aluminum, steel, glass, plastic"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 125942.0,
      "end_time": 127881.0,
      "text": "and printed circuit boards."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 127906.0,
      "end_time": 129828.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s called \"urban mining.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 129852.0,
      "end_time": 135560.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s now more efficient for us to mine materials from our waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 136310.0,
      "end_time": 140830.0,
      "text": "There is 10 times more gold, silver, platinum, palladium"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 140854.0,
      "end_time": 143210.0,
      "text": "in one ton of our electronics"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 143234.0,
      "end_time": 147192.0,
      "text": "than in one ton of ore mined from beneath the surface of the earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 149600.0,
      "end_time": 151171.0,
      "text": "In Agbogbloshie,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 151195.0,
      "end_time": 153275.0,
      "text": "weight is a form of currency."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 153918.0,
      "end_time": 158924.0,
      "text": "Devices are dissected to recover materials, parts and components"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 158948.0,
      "end_time": 160764.0,
      "text": "with incredible attention to detail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 160788.0,
      "end_time": 163916.0,
      "text": "down to the aluminum tips of electric plugs."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 165759.0,
      "end_time": 169884.0,
      "text": "But scrap dealers don&#39;t destroy components that are still functional."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 169908.0,
      "end_time": 173926.0,
      "text": "They supply them to repair workshops like this one in Agbogbloshie"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 173950.0,
      "end_time": 178442.0,
      "text": "and the tens of thousands of technicians across the country"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 178467.0,
      "end_time": 182558.0,
      "text": "that refurbish electrical and electronic equipment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 182582.0,
      "end_time": 186370.0,
      "text": "and sell them as used products to consumers that may not be able to buy"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 186394.0,
      "end_time": 188542.0,
      "text": "a new television or a new computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 190463.0,
      "end_time": 193677.0,
      "text": "Make no mistake about it, there are young hackers in Agbogbloshie --"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 193701.0,
      "end_time": 196545.0,
      "text": "and I mean that in the very best sense of that word --"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 197315.0,
      "end_time": 200110.0,
      "text": "that know not only how to take apart computers"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 200350.0,
      "end_time": 203286.0,
      "text": "but how to put them back together, how to give them new life."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 203817.0,
      "end_time": 207596.0,
      "text": "Agbogbloshie reminds us that making is a cycle."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 207620.0,
      "end_time": 210872.0,
      "text": "It extends to remaking and unmaking"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 210896.0,
      "end_time": 214828.0,
      "text": "in order to recover the materials that enable us to make something anew."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 215472.0,
      "end_time": 217400.0,
      "text": "We can learn from Agbogbloshie,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 217424.0,
      "end_time": 221275.0,
      "text": "where cobblers remake work boots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 221299.0,
      "end_time": 224639.0,
      "text": "where women collect plastic from all over the city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 224663.0,
      "end_time": 226161.0,
      "text": "sort it by type,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 226185.0,
      "end_time": 228134.0,
      "text": "shred it, wash it"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 228158.0,
      "end_time": 231248.0,
      "text": "and ultimately sell it back as feedstock to factories"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 231272.0,
      "end_time": 232640.0,
      "text": "to make new clothing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 232664.0,
      "end_time": 234430.0,
      "text": "new plastic buckets"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 234455.0,
      "end_time": 235616.0,
      "text": "and chairs."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 236444.0,
      "end_time": 238876.0,
      "text": "Steel is stockpiled separately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 238901.0,
      "end_time": 242831.0,
      "text": "where the carcasses of cars and microwaves and washing machines"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 242855.0,
      "end_time": 245149.0,
      "text": "become iron rods for new construction;"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 245173.0,
      "end_time": 247724.0,
      "text": "where roofing sheets become cookstoves;"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 247748.0,
      "end_time": 251298.0,
      "text": "where shafts from cars become chisels"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 251323.0,
      "end_time": 254830.0,
      "text": "that are used to scrap more objects;"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 254854.0,
      "end_time": 259127.0,
      "text": "where aluminum recovered from the radiators of fridges"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 259151.0,
      "end_time": 261874.0,
      "text": "and air conditioners"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 261898.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263234.0,
      "text": "are melted down"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 263258.0,
      "end_time": 267311.0,
      "text": "and use sand casting to make ornaments for the building industry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 267336.0,
      "end_time": 271267.0,
      "text": "for pots which are sold just down the street in the Agbogbloshie market"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 271291.0,
      "end_time": 277627.0,
      "text": "with a full array of locally made ovens, stoves and smokers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 277651.0,
      "end_time": 279189.0,
      "text": "which are used every day"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 279213.0,
      "end_time": 282619.0,
      "text": "to make the majority of palm nut soups,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 282643.0,
      "end_time": 284520.0,
      "text": "of tea and sugar breads,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 284544.0,
      "end_time": 286495.0,
      "text": "of grilled tilapia in the city."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 287322.0,
      "end_time": 292149.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re made in roadside workshops like this one by welders like Mohammed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 292173.0,
      "end_time": 294692.0,
      "text": "who recover materials from the waste stream"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 294716.0,
      "end_time": 296724.0,
      "text": "and use them to make all kinds of things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 296748.0,
      "end_time": 299707.0,
      "text": "like dumbbells for working out out of old car parts."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 299732.0,
      "end_time": 301224.0,
      "text": "But here&#39;s what&#39;s really cool:"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 301248.0,
      "end_time": 303587.0,
      "text": "the welding machines they use look like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 303611.0,
      "end_time": 307846.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re made by specially coiling copper"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 307870.0,
      "end_time": 313924.0,
      "text": "around electrical steel recovered from old transformer scrap."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 314630.0,
      "end_time": 318500.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s an entire industry just next to Agbogbloshie"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 318740.0,
      "end_time": 322653.0,
      "text": "making locally fabricated welding machines that power local fabrication."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 323549.0,
      "end_time": 327358.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s really cool as well is that there&#39;s a transfer of skills and knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 327382.0,
      "end_time": 328812.0,
      "text": "across generations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 328836.0,
      "end_time": 330810.0,
      "text": "from masters to apprentices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 330834.0,
      "end_time": 334553.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s done through active learning, through heuristic learning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 334577.0,
      "end_time": 336524.0,
      "text": "learning by doing and by making."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 336548.0,
      "end_time": 338765.0,
      "text": "And this stands in sharp contrast"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 338789.0,
      "end_time": 341198.0,
      "text": "to the experience of many students in school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 341222.0,
      "end_time": 342830.0,
      "text": "where lecturers lecture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 342855.0,
      "end_time": 345560.0,
      "text": "and students write things down and memorize them."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 346990.0,
      "end_time": 348974.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s boring, but the real problem is"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 348998.0,
      "end_time": 355111.0,
      "text": "this somehow preempts their latent or their inherent entrepreneurial power."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 355525.0,
      "end_time": 357784.0,
      "text": "They know books but not how to make stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 358872.0,
      "end_time": 362966.0,
      "text": "Four years ago, my cofounder Yasmine Abbas and I asked:"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 362990.0,
      "end_time": 365349.0,
      "text": "What would happen if we could couple"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 365373.0,
      "end_time": 369900.0,
      "text": "the practical know-how of makers in the informal sector"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 369330.0,
      "end_time": 373779.0,
      "text": "with the technical knowledge of students and young professionals"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 373803.0,
      "end_time": 375195.0,
      "text": "in STEAM fields --"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 375220.0,
      "end_time": 379170.0,
      "text": "science, technology, engineering, arts and mathematics --"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 379410.0,
      "end_time": 382406.0,
      "text": "to build a STEAM-powered innovation engine"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 382430.0,
      "end_time": 386487.0,
      "text": "to drive what we call \"Sankofa Innovation,\" which I&#39;ll explain."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 387656.0,
      "end_time": 391413.0,
      "text": "We took forays into the scrapyard"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 391437.0,
      "end_time": 394281.0,
      "text": "to look for what could be repurposed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 394305.0,
      "end_time": 397226.0,
      "text": "like DVD writers that could become laser etchers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 397250.0,
      "end_time": 400912.0,
      "text": "or the power supplies of old servers"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 400936.0,
      "end_time": 404890.0,
      "text": "for a start-up in Kumasi making 3D printers out of e-waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 405453.0,
      "end_time": 409186.0,
      "text": "The key was to bring together young people from different backgrounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 409211.0,
      "end_time": 412718.0,
      "text": "that ordinarily never have anything to do with each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 412742.0,
      "end_time": 416462.0,
      "text": "to have a conversation about how they could collaborate"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 416486.0,
      "end_time": 420594.0,
      "text": "and to test and develop new machines and tools"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 420619.0,
      "end_time": 424530.0,
      "text": "that could allow them to shred and strip copper instead of burning it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 424554.0,
      "end_time": 427707.0,
      "text": "to mold plastic bricks and tiles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 427732.0,
      "end_time": 433286.0,
      "text": "to build new computers out of components recovered from dead electronics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 433310.0,
      "end_time": 435158.0,
      "text": "to build a drone."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 436142.0,
      "end_time": 440770.0,
      "text": "And here you can see it flying for the first time in Agbogbloshie."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 442460.0,
      "end_time": 446433.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 447129.0,
      "end_time": 451306.0,
      "text": "Yasmine and I have collaborated with over 1,500 young people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 451330.0,
      "end_time": 454681.0,
      "text": "750 from STEAM fields,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 454705.0,
      "end_time": 459258.0,
      "text": "and over 750 grassroots makers and scrap dealers"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 459282.0,
      "end_time": 461327.0,
      "text": "from Agbogbloshie and beyond."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 461351.0,
      "end_time": 465858.0,
      "text": "They&#39;ve joined hands together to develop a platform"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 466665.0,
      "end_time": 469621.0,
      "text": "which they call Spacecraft,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 469645.0,
      "end_time": 473262.0,
      "text": "a hybrid physical and digital space for crafting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 473286.0,
      "end_time": 476227.0,
      "text": "more of a process than a product,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 476251.0,
      "end_time": 480135.0,
      "text": "an open architecture for making,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 480159.0,
      "end_time": 481840.0,
      "text": "which involves three parts:"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 481864.0,
      "end_time": 484868.0,
      "text": "a makerspace kiosk, which is prefab and modular;"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 484892.0,
      "end_time": 489940.0,
      "text": "tool kits which can be customized based on what makers want to make;"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 489118.0,
      "end_time": 490650.0,
      "text": "and a trading app."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 490674.0,
      "end_time": 494366.0,
      "text": "We built the app specifically with the needs of the scrap dealers"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 494390.0,
      "end_time": 495811.0,
      "text": "in mind first,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 495835.0,
      "end_time": 500308.0,
      "text": "because we realized that it was not enough to arm them with information"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 500333.0,
      "end_time": 501947.0,
      "text": "and upgraded technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 501971.0,
      "end_time": 505191.0,
      "text": "if we wanted them to green their recycling processes;"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 505215.0,
      "end_time": 507126.0,
      "text": "they needed incentives."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 507151.0,
      "end_time": 510794.0,
      "text": "Scrap dealers are always looking for new scrap and new buyers"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 510818.0,
      "end_time": 514999.0,
      "text": "and what interests them is finding buyers who will pay more"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 515230.0,
      "end_time": 517388.0,
      "text": "for clean copper than for burnt."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 518212.0,
      "end_time": 520962.0,
      "text": "We realized that in the entire ecosystem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 520986.0,
      "end_time": 523456.0,
      "text": "everyone was searching for something."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 523480.0,
      "end_time": 529524.0,
      "text": "Makers are searching for materials, parts, components, tools, blueprints"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 529548.0,
      "end_time": 531613.0,
      "text": "to make what it is they want to make."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 531962.0,
      "end_time": 535597.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re also finding a way to let customers and clientele"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 535621.0,
      "end_time": 537812.0,
      "text": "find out that they can repair a blender"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 537836.0,
      "end_time": 539306.0,
      "text": "or fix an iron"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 539330.0,
      "end_time": 542583.0,
      "text": "or, as we learned yesterday, to make a french fry machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 543496.0,
      "end_time": 546781.0,
      "text": "On the flip side, you find that there are end users"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 546806.0,
      "end_time": 550724.0,
      "text": "that are desperately looking for someone that can make them a french fry machine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 550748.0,
      "end_time": 554461.0,
      "text": "and you have scrap dealers who are looking how they can collect this scrap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 554485.0,
      "end_time": 558437.0,
      "text": "process it, and turn it back into an input for new making."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 558461.0,
      "end_time": 561503.0,
      "text": "We tried to untangle that knot of not knowing"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 561527.0,
      "end_time": 564958.0,
      "text": "to allow people to find what they need to make what they want to make."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 564982.0,
      "end_time": 568644.0,
      "text": "We prototyped the makerspace kiosk in Agbogbloshie,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 568668.0,
      "end_time": 571466.0,
      "text": "conceived as the opposite of a school:"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 571490.0,
      "end_time": 575324.0,
      "text": "a portal into experiential and experimental making"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 575348.0,
      "end_time": 577425.0,
      "text": "that connects local and global"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 577449.0,
      "end_time": 580931.0,
      "text": "and connects making with remaking and unmaking."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 581831.0,
      "end_time": 585135.0,
      "text": "We made a rule that everything had to be made from scratch"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 585159.0,
      "end_time": 587566.0,
      "text": "using only materials made in Ghana"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 587590.0,
      "end_time": 589454.0,
      "text": "or sourced from the scrapyard."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 590136.0,
      "end_time": 594750.0,
      "text": "The structures essentially are simple trusses which bolt together."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 594774.0,
      "end_time": 599577.0,
      "text": "It takes about two hours to assemble one module with semi-skilled labor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 599601.0,
      "end_time": 602715.0,
      "text": "and by developing tooling and jigs and rigs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 602739.0,
      "end_time": 606282.0,
      "text": "we were able to actually build these standardized parts"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 606306.0,
      "end_time": 609650.0,
      "text": "within this ecosystem of artisanal welders"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 609674.0,
      "end_time": 611598.0,
      "text": "with the precision of one millimeter --"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 612637.0,
      "end_time": 615671.0,
      "text": "of course, using made-in-Agbogbloshie welding machines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 615696.0,
      "end_time": 617139.0,
      "text": "as well as for the tools,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 617163.0,
      "end_time": 620778.0,
      "text": "which can lock, the toolboxes, and stack to make workbenches,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 620802.0,
      "end_time": 623430.0,
      "text": "and again, customized based on what you want to make."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 623827.0,
      "end_time": 626879.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve tested the app in Agbogbloshie"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 626903.0,
      "end_time": 630399.0,
      "text": "and are getting ready to open it up to other maker ecosystems."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 630826.0,
      "end_time": 634515.0,
      "text": "In six months, we&#39;ll have finished three years of testing"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 634539.0,
      "end_time": 636201.0,
      "text": "the makerspace kiosk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 636225.0,
      "end_time": 640322.0,
      "text": "which I have to admit, we&#39;ve subjected to some pretty horrific abuse."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 640346.0,
      "end_time": 642275.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s for a good cause,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 642299.0,
      "end_time": 644544.0,
      "text": "because based on the results of that testing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 644568.0,
      "end_time": 649883.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve been able to redesign an upgraded version of this makerspace."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 649907.0,
      "end_time": 655526.0,
      "text": "If a fab lab is large, expensive, and fixed in place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 655550.0,
      "end_time": 657574.0,
      "text": "think of this as the counterpoint:"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 658273.0,
      "end_time": 660910.0,
      "text": "something low-cost,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 660828.0,
      "end_time": 663991.0,
      "text": "which can be locally manufactured,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 664150.0,
      "end_time": 667610.0,
      "text": "which can be expanded and kitted out incrementally"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 667634.0,
      "end_time": 669929.0,
      "text": "as makers acquire resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 669953.0,
      "end_time": 672803.0,
      "text": "You can think of it as a toolshed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 672827.0,
      "end_time": 675952.0,
      "text": "where makers can come and check out tools"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 675976.0,
      "end_time": 678338.0,
      "text": "and take them via handcart"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 678362.0,
      "end_time": 681721.0,
      "text": "to wherever they want in the city to make what it is they want to make."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 681745.0,
      "end_time": 684692.0,
      "text": "And moving into the next phase, we&#39;re planning to also add"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 684716.0,
      "end_time": 687580.0,
      "text": "ceiling-mounted CNC bots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 687604.0,
      "end_time": 691381.0,
      "text": "which allow makers to cocreate together with robots."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 691405.0,
      "end_time": 693663.0,
      "text": "Ultimately, this is a kit of parts"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 693687.0,
      "end_time": 697560.0,
      "text": "which can be assembled locally within the informal sector"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 697800.0,
      "end_time": 698911.0,
      "text": "using standardized parts"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 698935.0,
      "end_time": 702641.0,
      "text": "which can be upgraded collectively through an open-source process."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 706800.0,
      "end_time": 709166.0,
      "text": "In totality, this entire makerspace system"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 709191.0,
      "end_time": 710905.0,
      "text": "tries to do five things:"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 710929.0,
      "end_time": 716129.0,
      "text": "to enable emerging makers to gather the resources they need"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 716153.0,
      "end_time": 718317.0,
      "text": "and the tools to make what they want to make;"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 718341.0,
      "end_time": 721199.0,
      "text": "to learn by doing and from others;"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 721223.0,
      "end_time": 724194.0,
      "text": "to produce more and better products;"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 724218.0,
      "end_time": 726942.0,
      "text": "to be able to trade to generate steady income;"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 726966.0,
      "end_time": 730803.0,
      "text": "and ultimately, to amplify not only their reputation as a maker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 730827.0,
      "end_time": 732377.0,
      "text": "but their maker potential."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 733266.0,
      "end_time": 737794.0,
      "text": "Sankofa is one of the most powerful Adinkra symbols of the Akan peoples"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 737818.0,
      "end_time": 739165.0,
      "text": "in Ghana and Cote d&#39;Ivoire,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 739190.0,
      "end_time": 744502.0,
      "text": "and it can be represented as a bird reaching onto its back to collect an egg,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 744526.0,
      "end_time": 745743.0,
      "text": "a symbol of power."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 747331.0,
      "end_time": 750469.0,
      "text": "It translates literally from the Twi as \"return and get it,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 750493.0,
      "end_time": 755226.0,
      "text": "and what this means is that if an individual or a community or a society"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 755250.0,
      "end_time": 760600.0,
      "text": "wants to have a successful future, they have to draw on the past."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 760300.0,
      "end_time": 763572.0,
      "text": "To acquire and master existing ways of doing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 763596.0,
      "end_time": 765914.0,
      "text": "access the knowledge of their ancestors."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 765938.0,
      "end_time": 767153.0,
      "text": "And this is very relevant"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 767177.0,
      "end_time": 771563.0,
      "text": "if we want to think about an inclusive future for Africa today."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 771587.0,
      "end_time": 773990.0,
      "text": "We have to start from the ground up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 774140.0,
      "end_time": 778170.0,
      "text": "mining what already works for methods and for models,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 778410.0,
      "end_time": 782173.0,
      "text": "and to think about how might we be able to connect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 782197.0,
      "end_time": 786309.0,
      "text": "in a kind of \"both-and,\" not \"either-or\" paradigm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 786333.0,
      "end_time": 789919.0,
      "text": "the innovation capacity of this growing network"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 789943.0,
      "end_time": 793188.0,
      "text": "of tech hubs and incubators across the continent"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 793212.0,
      "end_time": 797803.0,
      "text": "and to rethink beyond national boundaries and political boundaries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 797827.0,
      "end_time": 802117.0,
      "text": "to think about how we can network innovation in Africa"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 802141.0,
      "end_time": 804660.0,
      "text": "with the spirit of Sankofa"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 804684.0,
      "end_time": 809127.0,
      "text": "and the existing capacity of makers at the grassroots."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 810330.0,
      "end_time": 811821.0,
      "text": "If, in the future, someone tells you"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 811845.0,
      "end_time": 815385.0,
      "text": "Agbogbloshie is the largest e-waste dump in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 815409.0,
      "end_time": 817641.0,
      "text": "I hope you can correct them"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 817665.0,
      "end_time": 822209.0,
      "text": "and explain to them that a dump is a place where you throw things away"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 822233.0,
      "end_time": 823601.0,
      "text": "and leave them forever;"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 823625.0,
      "end_time": 825836.0,
      "text": "a scrapyard is where you take things apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 825860.0,
      "end_time": 829770.0,
      "text": "Waste is something that no longer has any value,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 829101.0,
      "end_time": 831735.0,
      "text": "whereas scrap is something that you recover"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 831759.0,
      "end_time": 835539.0,
      "text": "specifically to use it to remake something new."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 837523.0,
      "end_time": 838930.0,
      "text": "Making is a cycle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 839676.0,
      "end_time": 844719.0,
      "text": "and African makerspaces are already pioneering and leading"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 845969.0,
      "end_time": 848607.0,
      "text": "circular economy at the grassroots."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 849128.0,
      "end_time": 851373.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s make more and better together."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 851397.0,
      "end_time": 852564.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 852588.0,
      "end_time": 856360.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}